Description: 1. Breathe deeply into your chest and upper back. 2. Put your elbows on the bench and push your chest through to open up your upper spine. 3. Keep your abs tight and ribs pulled down. 4. Dont arch your lower back or flare your lower ribs out.

Name: Toy Soldier
Description: 1. Keep the heel of your planted leg on the ground, and keep it nearly locked out straight. 2. Brace the glute on the side of your planted leg and tuck your tailbone under to keep your pelvis from tilting. 3. Reach your opposite side hand towards your toes. 4. Dont bend the leg on your planted leg, come onto your toes or slouch your spine forward.

Name: Trap Bar Deadlift
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tightly braced and your ribs pulled downward. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move. 2. Lower to the bar while pushing your hips back and loading a light stretch into your hamstrings. 3. Keep your weight on your heels, your feet straight forward, your knees straight over your little toes and abs braced. 4. Pull upward while maintaining good positioning (knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels. 5. Keep your abs locked and ribs down at the top.

Name: Triceps Press-Down
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blades squeezed backward and down. 2. Press down without letting your shoulders pop forward during the press. 3. Keep your abs tight and your ribs pulled down so that your ribs don't flare out as you return upward.

Name: Turkish Get-up
Description: 1. Keep your arm vertical throughout the movement, and keep your eyes on the weight. 2. Move from elbow, to your hand, to a bridge position. 3. Move to your knee. 4. "Windshield wiper" your leg underneath to a lunge position. 5. With your weight on your forward heel and your ribs down, stand up to the top of the lunge. 6. "Ski" your trailing foot back and reverse the movement to return to the ground.

Name: Walking Dumbbell Cross-Carry
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tight and your ribs pulled down. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move, while keeping your shoulders back. 2. Press one weight overhead and keep the other at your side. 3. Carry the weights with tightly braced abs while keeping your shoulders back and your head neutral. 4. Don't slouch or let the weight pull you to the side.

Name: Walking Dumbbell Lunge
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Walking Farmer's Carry
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tight and your ribs pulled down. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move, and keep your shoulders back. 2. Carry the weight with tightly braced abs while keeping your shoulders back and your head neutral. 3. Don't slouch or let the weight pull you to the side.

Name: Walking Goblet Carry
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tight and your ribs pulled down. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move, and keep your shoulders back. 2. Carry the weight with tightly braced abs while keeping your shoulders back and your head neutral. 3. Don't slouch or let the weight pull you to the side.

Name: Walking Goblet Lunge
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Walking Fat Grip Farmer's Carry
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tight and your ribs pulled down. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move, while keeping your shoulders back. 2. Carry the weight with tightly braced abs while keeping your shoulders back and your head neutral. 3. Don't slouch or let the weight pull you to the side.

Name: Walking Goblet Heartbeat Carry
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tight and your ribs pulled down. Keep your tailbone tucked underneath you and your shoulders back. 2. Carry the weight with tightly braced abs while keeping your shoulders back and your head neutral. 3. Press the weight straight out and return it to your chest at regular intervals without losing your spinal position. 4. Don't slouch or let the weight pull you to the side.

Name: Walking Knee to Chest
Description: 1. Keep the heel of your planted leg on the ground and keep that leg straight. 2. Brace the glute on the side of your planted leg to keep your pelvis from tilting. 3. Pull one knee tightly to your chest while keeping the other leg extended straight. 4. Dont bend the leg on your planted leg, come onto your toes or slouch your spine forward.

Name: Walking Offset Dumbbell Lunge
Description: 1. The lighter of the two dumbbells goes in the hand on the same side as your forward leg. 2. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 3. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 4. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 5. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 6. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Walking Pull-Back Butt Kick
Description: 1. Keep the heel of your planted leg on the ground and keep that leg straight. Brace the glute on the side of your planted leg to keep your pelvis from tilting. 2. Pull one foot back and stretch your quad without leaning forward. 3. Keep your abs tight, your ribs down and tuck your tailbone under. 4. Dont arch your lower back, bend the leg on your planted leg, come onto your toes or slouch your spine forward.

Name: Walking Single-Arm Bottom-Up Kettlebell Racked Carry
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tight and your ribs pulled down. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move, and keep your shoulders back. 2. Carry the weight with tightly braced abs while keeping your shoulders back and your head neutral. 3. Don't slouch or let the weight pull you to the side.
VideoName: Walking Single-Arm Bottom-Up Kettlebell Racked Carry

Name: Walking Spiderman With Overhead Reach
Description: 1. Step slightly to the outside with your forward leg to make room for your elbow. 2. Keep your weight through your forward heel. 3. Keep your chest high and contract the glute on your trailing leg to get a good stretch in your hip flexor. 4. Keep your neck in line with the rest of your spine. 5. Slowly drive your hips forward to deepen the stretch, then reach overhead.

Name: Walking Two-Arm Waiters Carry
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tight and your ribs pulled down. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move, while keeping your shoulders back. 2. Press the weights overhead. 3. Carry the weights with tightly braced abs while keeping your shoulders back and your head neutral. 4. Don't slouch or let the weight pull you to the side.

Name: Walking Spiderman
Description: 1. Step slightly to the outside with your forward leg to make room for your elbow. 2. Keep your weight through your forward heel. 3. Keep your chest high and contract the glute on your trailing leg to get a good stretch in your hip flexor. 4. Keep your neck in line with the rest of your spine. 5. Slowly drive your hips forward to deepen the stretch.

Name: Walking Spiderman With Hip Lift
Description: 1. Step slightly to the outside with your forward leg to make room for your elbow. 2. Keep your weight through your forward heel. 3. Keep your chest high and contract the glute on your trailing leg to get a good stretch in your hip flexor. 4. Keep your neck in line with the rest of your spine. 5. Slowly drive your hips forward to deepen the stretch. 6. Lift your hips upward.

Name: Walking Waiter's Carry
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tight and your ribs pulled down. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move, while keeping your shoulders back. 2. Press the weight overhead. 3. Carry the weights with tightly braced abs while keeping your shoulders back and your head neutral. 4. Don't slouch or let the weight pull you to the side.

Name: Walking Spiderman With Overhead Reach and Hip Lift
Description: 1. Step slightly to the outside with your forward leg to make room for your elbow. 2. Keep your weight through your forward heel. 3. Keep your chest high and contract the glute on your trailing leg to get a good stretch in your hip flexor. 4. Keep your neck in line with the rest of your spine. 5. Slowly drive your hips forward to deepen the stretch, then reach overhead. 6. Lift your hips upward.
VideoName: Walking Spiderman With Overhead Reach and Hip Lift

Name: Wall Ankle Mobilization
Description: 1. Keep your heel rooted into the floor and press forward as far as you can while tracking your knee straight over your toes on the outside of your foot. This is mobilizing the ankle of your forward leg. 2. Dont lift your heel off the ground or push your knee towards the inside of your foot.

Name: Walking Warrior Lunge
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. At the bottom position, rotate your shoulders toward your forward knee. 5. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 6. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Wall Glute Iso March
Description: 1. Keep the front of your pelvis pulled towards your ribs, your abs tight and your tailbone tucked under. 2. Pull one knee straight towards your chest while keeping the other leg extended straight out by contracting your glute on that side. 3. Dont arch your lower back or flare your lower ribs out

Name: Wall Hip Flexor Mobilization
Description: 1. Use your arm to flex your knee as much as comfortably possible. 2. Use your abs to pull your ribs down, and keep your tailbone tucked under to protect your spine. 3. Contract the glute on your trailing-leg side in order to further stretch your hip flexors. 4. Dont arch your lower back or let your lower ribs flare out.

Name: Wall-Press Abs
Description: 1. Pull your ribs downward with your abs and hold them there. 2. Roll the front of your pelvis towards your ribs. 3. Press your lower back into the floor. 4. Don't lose that position as you cycle your legs.

Name: Warrior Lunge With Overhead Reach
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. At the bottom position, put your arms overhead (without arching your back) and rotate your shoulders toward your forward knee. 5. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 6. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Weighted Neutral-Grip Pull-Up
Description: 1. Fully extend your arms and let your shoulder blades spread at the bottom. 2. Pull the bar to your chest. 3. Finish the motion with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 4. Don't let your shoulders pop forward at the finish.

Name: Weighted Chin-Up
Description: 1. Fully extend your arms and let your shoulder blades spread at the bottom. 2. Pull the bar to your chest. 3. Finish the motion with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 4. Don't let your shoulders pop forward at the finish.

Name: Weighted Pushup
Description: 1. Only lower as far down as you can without your shoulders popping forward. 2. Squeeze your shoulder blades together and downward at the bottom of the rep. 3. Keep your abs tight and your ribs pulled down so that your lower back doesn't arch. 4. Finish by spreading your shoulder blades apart, with your shoulders pulled down away from your ears.

Name: Weighted Ring Pushup
Description: 1. Only lower as far down as you can without your shoulders popping forward. 2. Squeeze your shoulder blades together and downward at the bottom of the rep. 3. Keep your abs tight and your ribs pulled down so that your lower back doesn't arch. 4. Finish by spreading your shoulder blades apart, with your shoulders pulled down away from your ears.

Name: X-Band Walk
Description: 1. Lock your ribs down with your abs. 2. Tuck your tailbone between your knees. 3. Move from the hips, not your spine. 4. Don't rotate your feet outward.

Name: X-Band Box Walk
Description: 1. Lock your ribs down with your abs. 2. Tuck your tailbone between your knees. 3. Move from the hips, not your spine. 4. Don't rotate your feet outward.

Name: X-Lat Band Pull-Down
Description: 1. Keep your ribs down, abs tight and tailbone tucked between your knees. 2. Allow your shoulder blades to spread apart at the beginning as you cross your arms over. 3. Pull your hands back to your lower ribs, finishing with your shoulder blades locked inward and down. 4. Don't let your shoulder capsules shift forward at the finish of the movement.

Name: Yoga Downward Dog Stretch
Description: 1. Keep your lower ribs pulled down and reach overhead. 2. Stretch your lats out and drive your chest toward the ground. 3. Drive your heels to the ground. 4. You can move deeper into the stretch by alternately bending your knees.

Name: Yoga Plex
Description: 1. Step slightly to the outside with your forward leg to make room for your arm. 2. Keep your ribs down, tuck your tailbone under and contract the glute on your trailing leg to get a good stretch in your hip flexor. 3. Keep your neck in line with the rest of your spine. 4. With your chest high, stretch overhead and follow your hand with your eyes.

Name: Yoga Pushup
Description: 1. Keep your spine neutral, abs and glutes braced and hands shoulder-width apart. 2. Lower into the pushup by squeezing your shoulder blades together and down into your back pockets and keeping your elbows tucked in. 3. From the top of the pushup, push your hips into the air and drive your heels toward the ground to stretch your lats, chest, calves and hamstrings.

Name: 90/90 Wall Balloon-Breathing
Description: 1. Hook your heels into the wall with your hamstrings. 2. Tuck your tailbone between your knees. 3. Push your lower back into the floor. 4. Exhale fully, dropping your ribs down as far as they'll go. 5. Inhale without losing the ribs-down position and repeat.

Name: Ab Wheel Iso
Description: 1. Lock your ribs down with your abs. 2. Tuck your tailbone between your knees. 3. Do not let your lower back sag.

Name: Ab Wheel Rollout
Description: 1. Lock your ribs down with your abs. 2. Tuck your tailbone between your knees. 3. Do not let your lower back sag.

Name: Adductor Mobilization
Description: 1. Extend one leg out. 2. Push your hips back to lengthen your adductor. 3. Keep your spine neutral.

Name: Alternating Barbell Split Jump
Description: 1. Lower so that at the bottom your knees are both around 90 degrees. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Drive through your forward heel as you jump, and keep your knee tracked over your toes.

Name: Alternating Bodyweight Split Jump
Description: 1. Lower so that at the bottom your knees are both around 90 degrees. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Drive through your forward heel as you jump, and keep your knee tracked over your toes.

Name: Alternating Dumbbell Bench Press
Description: 1. Keep your abs locked tightly to prevent spinal rotation. 2. Keep your shoulder blades packed tightly inward and down at the bottom of each rep. 3. Only lower as far as you can without popping your shoulder capsule forward or losing stability, then press back up.

Name: Alternating Dumbbell Curl
Description: 1. Curl the weight without letting your shoulders pop forward. 2. Don't arch your lower back.

Name: Alternating Dumbell Split Jump
Description: 1. Lower so that at the bottom your knees are both around 90 degrees. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Drive through your forward heel as you jump, and keep your knee tracked over your toes.

Name: Alternating Goblet Reverse Lunge With Blocked Knee
Description: 1. Lower so that at the bottom your knees are both around 90 degrees. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.
VideoName: Alternating Goblet Reverse Lunge With Blocked Knee

Name: Alternating Lateral Lunge Walk
Description: 1. Lower so that at the bottom your knees are both around 90 degrees. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Anderson Front Squat
Description: 1. Set the bar at a height that allows you to get into a strong, stable bottom position. 2. Set up tightly in the bottom position with your weight in your heels, your feet straight forward, your knees straight over your little toes and abs braced. 3. Drive the bar upward while maintaining good positioning (knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels.

Name: Assisted Bodyweight Squat to Box
Description: 1. Lock your ribs down with your abs. 2. Keep your feet straight ahead. 3. Push your hips back onto the box. 4. Keep your knees straight out over your toes.

Name: Assisted Lateral Squat
Description: 1. Keep your heel down. 2. Keep your knee pointed straight ahead over your toes. 3. Only lower as far as you comfortably can.

Name: Assisted Reverse Lunge With Blocked Knee
Description: 1. Lower so that at the bottom your knees are both around 90 degrees. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. Only pull on the object in front of you with enough force to stay balanced. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.
VideoName: Assisted Reverse Lunge With Blocked Knee

Name: Band Press-Down
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blades squeezed backward and down. 2. Press down without letting your shoulders pop forward during the press. 3. Keep your abs tight and your ribs pulled down so that your ribs don't flare out as you return upward.

Name: Band Pull-Apart
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blades pulled downward away from your ears throughout the movement. 2. Let your shoulder blades spread apart with your hands in front of your body. 3. Finish the rep by squeezing your shoulder blades together as you pull the band apart.

Name: Band-Assisted Chin-Up
Description: 1. Fully extend your arms and let your shoulder blades spread at the bottom. 2. Pull the bar to your chest. 3. Finish the motion with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 4. Don't let your shoulders pop forward at the finish.

Name: Band-Assisted Inverted Row
Description: 1. Fully extend your arms and let your shoulder blades spread apart at the bottom. 2. Pull the bar to the lower part of your ribcage. 3. Finish the motion with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 4. Don't let your shoulders pop forward at the finish.

Name: Band-Assisted Neutral-Grip Pull-Up
Description: 1. Fully extend your arms and let your shoulder blades spread at the bottom. 2. Pull the bar to your chest. 3. Finish the motion with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 4. Don't let your shoulders pop forward at the finish.

Name: Band-Assisted Pull-Up
Description: 1. Fully extend your arms and let your shoulder blades spread at the bottom. 2. Pull the bar to your chest. 3. Finish the motion with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 4. Don't let your shoulders pop forward at the finish.

Name: Band-Assisted Pushup
Description: 1. Only lower as far down as you can without your shoulders popping forward. 2. Squeeze your shoulder blades together and downward at the bottom of the rep. 3. Keep your abs tight and your ribs pulled down so that your lower back doesn't arch. 4. Finish by spreading your shoulder blades apart, with your shoulders pulled down away from your ears.

Name: Band-Resisted Ab Wheel Iso
Description: 1. Lock your ribs down with your abs. 2. Tuck your tailbone between your knees. 3. Do not let your lower back sag.

Name: Band-Resisted Goblet Squat
Description: 1. Set up tightly in the bottom position with your weight in your heels, your feet straight forward, your knees straight over your little toes and abs braced. 3. Squat upward while maintaining good positioning (knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels.

Name: Band-Resisted Pull-Up
Description: 1. Fully extend your arms and let your shoulder blades spread at the bottom. 2. Pull the bar to your chest. 3. Finish the motion with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 4. Don't let your shoulders pop forward at the finish.

Name: Band-Resisted Scapular Pushup
Description: 1. Keep your abs tight and your ribs pulled down so that your lower back doesn't arch. 2 Squeeze your shoulder blades together and down at the bottom. 3. Finish by spreading your shoulder blades apart, with your shoulders pulled down away from your ears.

Name: Band-Resisted Ring Pushup
Description: 1. Only lower as far down as you can without your shoulders popping forward. 2. Squeeze your shoulder blades together and downward at the bottom of the rep. 3. Name: Band-Resisted Squat
Description: 1. Lock your ribs down with your abs. 2. Keep your feet straight ahead. 3. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move 4. Keep your knees straight out over your toes.

Name: Banded Curl
Description: 1. Curl the band without letting your shoulders pop forward. 2. Don't arch your lower back.

Name: Banded External Rotation at 30 Degrees Abduction

Name: Banded Face Pull
Description: 1. Let your shoulder blades spread apart when your arms are forward. 2. Pull the band towards your face and finish with your thumbs pointed upward and your shoulder blades squeezed together and downward. 3. Don't arch your back or let your ribs flare out during the movement.

Name: Banded Hip Extension
Description: 1. Keep your ribs pulled down and your abs tight so that your lower back doesn't arch. 2. Drive through your heels and raise your hips upward. 3. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move.

Name: Banded No Money
Description: 1. Keep your abs tight and your ribs down so that your back doesn't arch. 2. Bring your hands together with your palms up. 3. Pull the band apart and finish by squeezing your shoulder blades together and downward.

Name: Banded Pull-Down
Description: 1. Fully extend your arms and let your shoulder blades spread at the start. 2. Pull your hands to your chest. 3. Finish the motion with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 4. Don't let your shoulders pop forward at the finish.

Name: Banded Scapular Protraction
Description: 1. Start with your shoulder blades shrugged downward and squeezed together. 2. While keeping your shoulder blades down away from your ears, spread them apart as far as you can.

Name: Barbell Back Squat
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tightly braced and your ribs pulled downward. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move 2. Lower down with your weight in your heels, your feet straight forward, your knees straight over your little toes and abs braced. 3. Squat upward while maintaining good positioning (knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels.

Name: Barbell Bench Press
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blades packed tightly together and down at the bottom of each rep. 2. Only lower as far as you can without popping your shoulder capsule forward or losing stability, then press back up.

Name: Barbell Bench Press From Pins
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blades packed tightly together and down at the bottom of each rep. 2. Only lower as far as you can without popping your shoulder capsule forward or losing stability, then press back up.

Squat upward while maintaining good positioning (knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels.

Name: Barbell Curl
Description: 1. Curl the weight without letting your shoulders pop forward. 2. Don't arch your lower back.

Name: Barbell Deadlift
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tightly braced and your ribs pulled downward. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move. 2. Lower to the bar while pushing your hips back and loading a light stretch into your hamstrings. 3. Keep your weight on your heels, your feet straight forward, your knees straight over your little toes and abs braced. 4. Pull upward while maintaining good positioning (knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels. 5. Keep your abs locked and ribs down at the top.

Name: Barbell Floor Press
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blades packed tightly together and down at the bottom of each rep. 2. Press upward.

Name: Barbell Front Squat
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tightly braced and your ribs pulled downward. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move 2. Lower down with your weight in your heels, your feet straight forward, your knees straight over your little toes and abs braced. 3. Squat upward while maintaining good positioning (knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels.

Name: Barbell Front Squat Iso
Description: 1. Keep your abs tightly braced in order to keep your ribs down. 2. Hold the position with good bracing so that your lower back doesn't arch.

Name: Barbell Front Squat to Box
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tightly braced and your ribs pulled downward. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move 2. Lower down with your weight in your heels, your feet straight forward, your knees straight over your little toes and abs braced. 3. Put only 50% of your weight on the box and then squat upward while maintaining good positioning (knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels.

Name: Barbell Glute Bridge
Description: 1. Keep your ribs pulled down and your abs tight so that your lower back doesn't arch. 2. Drive through your heels and raise your hips upward. 3. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move.

Name: Barbell Hip Thrust
Description: 1. Keep your ribs pulled down and your abs tight so that your lower back doesn't arch. 2. Drive through your heels and raise your hips upward. 3. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move.

Name: Barbell Overhead Shrug
Description: 1. Keep your abs tightly braced and your ribs down so that your back doesn't arch. 2. Shrug the bar upward.

Name: Barbell Push Press
Description: 1. Keep your abs tight and ribs pulled down to stabilize your spine. 2. Dip your knees slightly while keeping your weight on your heels and drive upward. 3. Use the momentum to assist as you lock the bar overhead without arching your back.

Name: Barbell Reverse Lunge
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Barbell Reverse Lunge With a Front Squat Grip
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.
VideoName: Barbell Reverse Lunge With a Front Squat Grip

Name: Barbell Romanian Deadlift
Description: 1. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move. 2. Push your hips back until you get a light stretch in your hamstrings. 3. Return upward and lock your hips out while tucking your tailbone downward between your knees. 4. Don't let your lower back arch during the movement.

Name: Barbell Slideboard Reverse Lunge
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Barbell Split Squat
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Barbell Sumo Deadlift
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tightly braced and your ribs pulled downward. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move. 2. Lower to the bar while pushing your hips back and loading a light stretch into your hamstrings. 3. Keep your weight on your heels, your knees straight over your toes and abs braced. 4. Pull upward while maintaining good positioning (knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels. 5. Keep your abs locked and ribs down at the top.

Name: Bent-Over Dumbbell Row
Description: 1. Keep your ribs down and abs tight so that you don't arch your lower back too much. 2. Pull the weight back, finishing with your shoulder blade locked inward and down. 3. Don't let your shoulder capsule shift forward at the finish of the movement. 4. Let your shoulder blade stretch forward as you lower the weight.

Name: Bird Dog
Description: 1. This is a reciprocal movement, so the left arm and right leg move at once, and vice versa. 2. While kneeling on all-fours, exhale fully and feel your oblique abs lock your ribs down. 3. Keep your abs tightly braced to hold this ribs-down position and tuck your tailbone under. 4. While holding this position, reach your arm straight forward and your opposite leg straight behind you. 5. Keep your abs tight and do not let your ribs flare or arch your lower back as you lock out your shoulder blade and opposite-side glute.

Name: Bodyweight Cross-Over Step-Up
Description: 1. Keep your ribs down and don't arch your back as you're moving. 2. Step across your body while keeping your hips square. 3. Keep your weight rooted through your heel - Don't come up onto your toes. 4. Step up without rotating your hips open or arching your back.

Name: Bodyweight Get-Up
Description: 1. Keep your arm vertical throughout the movement, and keep your eyes on your hand. 2. Move from elbow, to your hand, to a bridge position. 3. Move to your knee. 4. "Windshield wiper" your leg underneath to a lunge position. 5. With your weight on your forward heel and your ribs down, stand up to the top of the lunge. 6. "Ski" your trailing foot back and reverse the movement to return to the ground.

Name: Bodyweight Lateral Lunge With Assistance
Description: 1. Keep your heel down. 2. Keep your knee pointed straight ahead over your toes. 3. Only lower as far as you comfortably can.

Name: Bodyweight Lateral Squat
Description: 1. Keep your heel down. 2. Keep your knee pointed straight ahead over your toes. 3. Only lower as far as you comfortably can.

Name: Bodyweight Reverse Lunge With Blocked Knee
Description: 1. Keep your heel down. 2. Keep your knee pointed straight ahead over your toes. 3. Only lower as far as you comfortably can.
VideoName: Bodyweight Reverse Lunge With Blocked Knee

Name: Bodyweight Split Squat With Blocked Knee
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.
VideoName: Bodyweight Split Squat With Blocked Knee

Name: Bodyweight Squat Thrust
Description: 1. Squat down with your heels on the ground. 2. Squat up while keeping your heels down and your abs braced. 3. Don't arch your lower back at the top.

Name: Bodyweight Squat to Box
Description: 1. Lock your ribs down with your abs. 2. Keep your feet straight ahead. 3. Push your hips back onto the box. 4. Keep your knees straight out over your toes.

Name: Bodyweight Step-Up
Description: 1. Keep your ribs down and don't arch your back as you're moving. 2. Step onto the box while keeping your hips square. 3. Keep your weight rooted through your heel - Don't come up onto your toes. 4. Step up without rotating your hips open or arching your back. 5. Keep your knee tracking straight over your toes the whole time - don't let it collapse inward.

Name: Bowler Squat
Description: 1. Keep your weight rooted through your heel, your ribs down and have a slight bend in your knee. 2. Hinge forward at the hips by pushing your hips back until you feel a light stretch in your hamstring. 3. Keep your hips level - Don't roll them open. 4. At the bottom, reach across the centerline of your body towards the toes on your opposite foot. 5. Return without arching your back or flaring your ribs out.

Name: Brady Band Series
Description: 1. This is four separate movements, each done for reps. 2. Focus on keeping your abs braced and your ribs down throughout the movements.

Name: Brady Band Series - Without Band
Description: 1. This is four separate movements, each done for reps. 2. Focus on keeping your abs braced and your ribs down throughout the movements.

Name: Burpee
Description: 1. Squat down with your feet straight forward, your heels on the ground and your knees tracking over your toes. 2. Jump back to a plank position, and land with your abs braced and without arching your back. 3. Drop into the pushup while keeping your tailbone tucked under and squeezing your shoulder blades together and down to your back pockets. 4. Finish the pushup and jump back to the squat position with your heels on the ground, knees straight forward and feet straight. 5. Jump upward and drop down to repeat.

Name: Burpee Without Pushup
Description: 1. Squat down with your feet straight forward, your heels on the ground and your knees tracking over your toes. 2. Jump back to a plank position, and land with your abs braced and without arching your back. 3. Keep your ribs down and your tailbone tucked under while in the plank position to keep your lower back from arching. 4. Jump back to the squat position with your heels on the ground, knees straight forward and feet straight. 5. Jump upward and drop down to repeat.

Name: Cable External Rotation at 30 Degrees Abduction
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blade packed inward and down toward your back pockets. 2 Rotate your arm while moving from the upper arm only. 3. Don't let your shoulder capsule shift forward during the movement.
VideoName: Cable External Rotation at 30 Degrees Abduction

Name: Cable External Rotation at 90 Degrees Abduction
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blade packed inward and down toward your back pockets. 2 Rotate your arm while moving from the upper arm only. 3. Don't let your shoulder capsule shift forward during the movement.
VideoName: Cable External Rotation at 90 Degrees Abduction

Name: Cable External Rotation on Knee
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blade packed inward and down toward your back pockets. 2 Rotate your arm while moving from the upper arm only. 3. Don't let your shoulder capsule shift forward during the movement.

Name: Cable Pull-Down
Description: 1. Fully extend your arms and let your shoulder blades spread at the bottom. 2. Pull the bar to your chest. 3. Finish the motion with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 4. Don't let your shoulders pop forward at the finish.

Name: Chest-Supported Dumbbell Row
Description: 1. Keep your ribs down and abs tight so that you don't arch your lower back too much. 2. Pull the weight back, finishing with your shoulder blade locked inward and down. 3. Don't let your shoulder capsule shift forward at the finish of the movement. 4. Let your shoulder blade stretch forward as you lower the weight.

Name: Chin-Up
Description: 1. Fully extend your arms and let your shoulder blades spread at the bottom. 2. Pull the bar to your chest. 3. Finish the motion with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 4. Don't let your shoulders pop forward at the finish.

Name: Close-Grip Barbell Bench Press
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blades packed tightly together and down at the bottom of each rep. 2. Only lower as far as you can without popping your shoulder capsule forward or losing stability, then press back up.

Name: Close-Grip Pushup
Description: 1. Only lower as far down as you can without your shoulders popping forward. 2. Squeeze your shoulder blades together and downward at the bottom of the rep. 3. Keep your abs tight and your ribs pulled down so that your lower back doesn't arch. 4. Finish by spreading your shoulder blades apart, with your shoulders pulled down away from your ears.

Name: Cross-Body Lat Mobilization
Description: 1. Keep your abs braced and your ribs down so that your back doesn't arch during the movement. 2. Cross your body to the side until you feel a stretch in the side of your torso.

Name: Dead Bug
Description: 1. Pull your ribs downward with your abs and hold them there. 2. Roll the front of your pelvis towards your ribs. 3. Press your lower back into the floor. 4. Don't lose that position as you move your arms and legs.

Name: Dead Bug With Legs Only
Description: 1. Pull your ribs downward with your abs and hold them there. 2. Roll the front of your pelvis towards your ribs. 3. Press your lower back into the floor. 4. Don't lose that position as you move your legs.

Name: Deep Neck Flexor Activation and Suboccipital Stretch
Description: 1. With your upper back and the back of your head against the wall, keep your teeth together and tuck your chin back as if giving yourself double chins. 2. You should feel the deep muscles in your neck activate and a light stretch in the base of your skull.
VideoName: Deep Neck Flexor Activation and Suboccipital Stretch

Name: Deep Squat Wall Stretch
Description: 1. Keep your hips against the wall. 2. Keep your feet straight ahead. 3. Drive your knees outward.

Name: Dragon Flag
Description: 1. Exhale completely while tucking your tailbone under so that your ribs lock downward as far as they'll go. 2. Inhale partially while maintaing tightly braced abs in order to keep your ribs down. 3. Keep your tailbone tucked under and the front of your pelvis pulled towards your chest as you lift off the bench. 4. Do not let your lower back arch at all.

Name: Dumbbell 1 1/4 Full Squat
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tightly braced and your ribs pulled downward. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move. 2. Lower down with your weight in your heels, your feet straight forward, your knees straight over your little toes and abs braced. 3. Squat upward while maintaining good positioning with your knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels. 4. Once you're 1/4 of the way up, drop back down to the bottom before squatting all the way up.

Name: Dumbbell Bench Press
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blades packed tightly together and down at the bottom of each rep. 2. Only lower as far as you can without popping your shoulder capsule forward or losing stability, then press back up.

Name: Dumbbell Cross-Over Step-Up
Description: 1. Keep your ribs down and don't arch your back as you're moving. 2. Step across your body while keeping your hips square. 3. Keep your weight rooted through your heel - Don't come up onto your toes. 4. Step up without rotating your hips open or arching your back.

Name: Dumbbell Curl
Description: 1. Curl the weight without letting your shoulders pop forward. 2. Don't arch your lower back.

Name: Dumbbell External Rotation on Knee
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blade packed inward and down toward your back pockets. 2 Rotate your arm while moving from the upper arm only. 3. Don't let your shoulder capsule shift forward during the movement.

Name: Dumbbell Floor Press
Description: 1. Keep your shoulder blades packed tightly together and down at the bottom of each rep. 2. Only lower as far as you can without popping your shoulder capsule forward or losing stability, then press back up.

Name: Dumbbell Full Squat
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tightly braced and your ribs pulled downward. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move 2. Lower down with your weight in your heels, your feet straight forward, your knees straight over your little toes and abs braced. 3. Squat upward while maintaining good positioning with your knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels.

Name: Hammer Curl
Description: 1. Curl the weight without letting your shoulders pop forward. 2. Don't arch your lower back.

Name: Dumbbell Overhead Shrug
Description: 1. Keep your abs tightly braced and your ribs down so that your back doesn't arch. 2. Shrug the weights upward.

Name: Dumbbell Push Press
Description: 1. Keep your abs tight and ribs pulled down to stabilize your spine. 2. Dip your knees slightly while keeping your weight on your heels and drive upward. 3. Use the momentum to assist as you lock the weights overhead without arching your back.

Name: Dumbbell Reverse Lunge
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Dumbbell Reverse Lunge From Deficit
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Dumbbell Reverse Lunge to Romanian Deadlift
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes. 6. After the lunge, hinge forward at the hips by pushing your hips back without rolling them open. 7. Keep your ribs down and don't arch your back. 8. Stop when you get a slight stretch in your hamstring, then return to the start.
VideoName: Dumbbell Reverse Lunge to Romanian Deadlift

Name: Dumbbell Reverse Lunge With Blocked Knee
Description: 1. Block your knee so that it doesn't track forward past the middle of your foot. 2. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 3. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 4. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 5. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 6. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.
VideoName: Dumbbell Reverse Lunge With Blocked Knee

Name: Dumbbell Romanian Deadlift
Description: 1. Keep your ribs pulled down and abs tightly braced to keep your lower back from arching. 2. Push your hips back until you get a light stretch in your hamstrings. 3. Return upward and lock your hips out. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move. 4. Don't let your lower back arch during the movement.

Name: Dumbbell Slideboard Reverse Lunge
Description: 1. Lower with your weight on your forward heel. 2. Don't let your hips open up at the bottom. Keep them squared forward. 3. Keep your lower back neutral by pulling your ribs down with your abs and keeping your abs tight. Don't let your back arch. 4. Drive upward with your weight rooted through the heel of your forward foot. 5. Keep your knee tracked straight ahead over your toes.

Name: Dumbbell Split Squat
Description: 1. Lock your ribs down with your abs. 2. Keep your pelvis square. 3. Keep your weight through your forward heel. 4. Forward knee and bottom knee should be at 90 degrees at the bottom.

Name: Dumbbell Squat Thrust
Description: 1. Squat down with your feet straight forward, your heels on the ground and your knees tracking over your toes. 2. Squat upward while pressing the weights overhead. 3. Keep your ribs down and your abs tight so that your lower back doesn't arch when the weights are overhead.

Name: Dumbbell Step-Up
Description: 1. Keep your ribs down and don't arch your back as you're moving. 2. Step onto the box while keeping your hips square. 3. Keep your weight rooted through your heel - Don't come up onto your toes. 4. Step up without rotating your hips open or arching your back. 5. Keep your knee tracking straight over your toes the whole time - don't let it collapse inward.

Name: Dumbbell Sumo Deadlift
Description: 1. Begin with your abs tightly braced and your ribs pulled downward. Think of using your abs to control the space between your ribs and the front of your pelvis, and don't let them get further apart as you move. 2. Lower to the dumbbell while pushing your hips back and loading a light stretch into your hamstrings. 3. Keep your weight on your heels, your feet straight forward, your knees straight over your toes and abs braced. 4. Pull upward while maintaining good positioning (knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels. 5. Keep your abs locked and ribs down at the top.

Name: Dynamic Blackburn
Description: 1. Keep your tailbone tucked under and your ribs pulled down so that your lower back doesn't arch. 2. Keep your head and neck neutral and don't arch your neck. 3. Move from the shoulder blades and go from having your palms together while overhead to having your palms up while behind your back.

Name: Eccentric Chin-Up
Description: 1. Jump or step up to the top of the bar. 2. Pull the bar to your chest with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 3. Don't let your shoulders pop forward. 4. Slowly lower down.

Name: Eccentric Pull-Up
Description: 1. Jump or step up to the top of the bar. 2. Pull the bar to your chest with your shoulder blades squeezed fully together and down and your elbows just behind your ribs. 3. Don't let your shoulders pop forward. 4. Slowly lower down.

Name: Elbow Plank Bodysaw
Description: 1. Lock your ribs down with your abs. 2. Tuck your tailbone between your knees. 3. Do not let your lower back sag. 4. Move your elbows without losing your positioning.

Name: Explosive Pushup
Description: 1. Only lower as far down as you can without your shoulders popping forward. 2. Squeeze your shoulder blades together and downward at the bottom of the rep. 3. Keep your abs tight and your ribs pulled down so that your lower back doesn't arch. 4. Finish by pushing upward explosively so that your hands leave the ground.

Name: Face Pull
Description: 1. Let your shoulder blades spread apart when your arms are forward. 2. Pull the cable towards your face and finish with your thumbs pointed upward and your shoulder blades squeezed together and downward. 3. Don't arch your back or let your ribs flare out during the movement.

Name: Feet-Elevated Band-Resisted Pushup
Description: 1. Only lower as far down as you can without your shoulders popping forward. 2. Squeeze your shoulder blades together and downward at the bottom of the rep. 3. Keep your abs tight and your ribs pulled down so that your lower back doesn't arch. 4. Finish by spreading your shoulder blades apart, with your shoulders pulled down away from your ears.

Name: Feet-Elevated Pushup
Description: 1. Only lower as far down as you can without your shoulders popping forward. 2. Squeeze your shoulder blades together and downward at the bottom of the rep. 3. Keep your abs tight and your ribs pulled down so that your lower back doesn't arch. 4. Finish by spreading your shoulder blades apart, with your shoulders pulled down away from your ears.

Name: Feet-Elevated Pushup to Single-Arm Support

Name: Feet-Elevated Side Plank
Description: 1. Position your spine by locking your ribs down in an exhaled position with your abs. 2. Keep your tailbone tucked under and your ribs pulled down throughout the movement. 3. Hold for the allotted time.

Squat upward while maintaining good positioning with your knees straight forward, neutral spine, weight through heels. 4.

Name: Lat and Triceps Stretch
Description: 1. Get movement through the shoulder, not the spine.

Name: Lying Dumbbell Triceps Extension

Name: Mountain Climber
